  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If the block's gas limit is lower than the parent's, the check will pass even if the diff is greater than parent's block limit divided by 1024.\n\n~~https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/core/block_processor.go#L263~~\n\nIf **a** is negative here, which happens if block's gas limit < parent's gas limit, then the comparison will always pass, allowing that gas limit.\n\nThis is fixed by taking the absolute value of block's gas limit subtracted by parent's gas limit: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/594\n\nThis also makes the comparison check that the diff is strictly smaller than the allowed value, according to (8) in https://ethereum.etherpad.mozilla.org/106?\n",
